Here are 15 objective question-answer pairs based on the provided document page:

1. Q: What is the purpose of a Personalausweis (PA)?
A: A PA is an official identity document that proves your identity and nationality.

2. Q: Who can apply for a new PA?
A: Citizens of Germany who have never had a PA or whose previous PA has been lost, stolen, or changed their name.

3. Q: What are the biometric data required for a PA application?
A: A photo, signature, and fingerprints.

4. Q: Can I use a self-service terminal to capture my biometric data?
A: Yes, you can use one of our Speed Capture Terminals (SCT) to capture your biometric data. The cost is €6.

5. Q: How long do the captured biometric data remain stored on the SCT?
A: The data are deleted within 60 minutes if not retrieved by a staff member or within 12 hours.

6. Q: Can I use my PA for travel purposes?
A: Yes, your PA can be used as an identity document for international travel.

7. Q: Is there a fee for the PA application process?
A: Yes, there are various fees associated with the PA application process, including €30 for consular or diplomatic services abroad.

8. Q: Can I get a temporary PA if mine has been lost or stolen?
A: Yes, you can apply for a vorläufiger Personalausweis (VPA) as an emergency measure.

9. Q: How do I obtain a VPA?
A: You need to provide proof of identity and fill out the application form at a Hamburg Service center.

10. Q: Is there a fee for the VPA application process?
A: Yes, there is a fee for the VPA application process, which varies depending on your circumstances.

11. Q: Can I apply for a PA online?
A: No, you need to visit a Hamburg Service center in person to apply for a PA.

12. Q: What are the opening hours of the Hamburg Service centers?
A: The centers are open Monday to Friday from 8 am to 2 pm by appointment only.

13. Q: Can I use my credit card or Girocard to pay for the PA application process?
A: Yes, you can use your credit card or Girocard to pay for the PA application process.

14. Q: Are there any special services available for people with disabilities?
A: Yes, our Speed Capture Terminals are accessible and barrier-free.

15. Q: Can I get a refund if I withdraw my PA application?
A: No, fees paid as part of the PA application process are non-refundable.